  "body": "The functionality is there but only triggered for known networks. Expose option to read and parse bootnode ENRs file.\r\n\r\n**Spec**\r\n\r\nAdd flag `--bootnodesFile` in the beacon command, specifically here https://github.com/ChainSafe/lodestar/blob/240085facb5e542defd8d190d5d2a0abbc574ecf/packages/cli/src/cmds/beacon/options.ts#L156\r\n\r\nThis flag's path must be processed with the same path manipulation logic from `getBeaconPaths()` https://github.com/ChainSafe/lodestar/blob/240085facb5e542defd8d190d5d2a0abbc574ecf/packages/cli/src/cmds/beacon/paths.ts#L29\r\n\r\nParsing logic may be based on https://github.com/ChainSafe/lodestar/blob/240085facb5e542defd8d190d5d2a0abbc574ecf/packages/cli/src/networks/index.ts#L67\r\n\r\nand be able to parse any of this file formats\r\n```\r\n### Ethereum Node Records\r\n- enr:-KG4QOWkRj\r\n```\r\n```\r\n### Ethereum Node Records\r\n- \"enr:-KG4QOWkRj\"\r\n```\r\n```\r\nenr:-KG4QOWkRj\r\n```\r\n```\r\n\"enr:-KG4QOWkRj\"\r\n```\r\n\r\nParsed bootnode ENRs must be \"injected\" into the beacon option `network.discv5.bootEnrs` like done here https://github.com/ChainSafe/lodestar/blob/240085facb5e542defd8d190d5d2a0abbc574ecf/packages/cli/src/networks/index.ts#L50\r\n\r\nIf `bootnodesFile` is specified it MUST overwrite the bootnodes injected by https://github.com/ChainSafe/lodestar/blob/240085facb5e542defd8d190d5d2a0abbc574ecf/packages/cli/src/networks/index.ts#L41\r\n\r\n**Tests**\r\n\r\n- Test parsing of sample files with at least the four formats outlined above\r\n- Ensure param overwrite rules work as expected and the resulting `beaconNodeOptions` object contains the target bootnode ENRs",
